<div xmlns="" class="main">
<h3>
<img src="img/flow_chart_h3_01.gif" alt="Steps to application" width="510" height="33" />
</h3>
<p>
<img src="img/flow_chart_pic01.gif" alt="Steps to application" width="490" height="345" />
</p>
<p>Steps 4, 6, and 7 will be done by JPIX.<br />
			he remaining steps are to be done by the customer. </p>
<h4>
<img src="img/flow_chart_h4_01.gif" alt="(1)Location of the BGP router" width="510" height="22" />
</h4>
<p>We require the customer to prepare a router that supports the BGP4  protocol. The connection interface, the demarcation of responsibility,  and prices may vary depending upon where the router is installed.</p>
<p class="ifsection">Under circumstances where the router is located in either the KDDI Otemachi building, NTT Data Otemachi Building(Broadband Tower), @Tokyo Chuo Center, TY2 Tokyo IBX Center , NTT Data Dojima Building , KDDI Nagoya Building and ComSpaceⅠ:</p>
<p style="padding:0 1.5em">Since there is a JPIX switch installed in these locations, basically  connection can be made using in-house cabling. However, there may be  some cases where connection cannot be made due to your router  collocation sites or interfaces. For more detailed information, please  contact our <a href="../contact/index.html">sales department</a>.<br />
JPIX collocation service are provided within the KDDI Otemachi Building  and Telecom Center Building. Those who desire a new collocation space  should request this location.</p>
<p class="ifsection">In cases with routers installed in buildings other than the above mentioned seven buildings (and in the above mentioned buildings where connection is not possible with in-house cabling):</p>
<p style="padding:0 1.5em">Connections can be made by installing an ATM leased circuit or Ethernet  leased circuit (a network interface using an Ethernet interface) into  KDDI Otemachi Building (JPIX Otemachi). Please contact local carrier in  regards to the possibility of installing such circuits into KDDI  Otemachi Bldg.</p>
<h4>
<img src="img/flow_chart_h4_02.gif" alt="(2)Connection Interface" width="510" height="22" />
</h4>
<p>You will select the appropriate IX port according to your traffic. At  present, the services we provide are 10Gigabit Ethernet (10Gbps),  Gigabit Ethernet (1Gbps) and Fast Ethernet (100Mbps) ports. The  provided port interfaces are usually 10GBase-LR, 1000Base-SX,  100Base-FX, or 100Base-TX interfaces. This may vary among the different  collocation sites. For details please contact our <a href="../contact/index.html">sales department</a>.</p>
<h4>
<img src="img/flow_chart_h4_03.gif" alt="(3)Steps until IX connection" width="510" height="22" />
</h4>
<p>As soon as the location of the router for connecting to the IX and the  interface is decided upon, an quotation will be sent along with copy of  the terms and conditions. After reading through the terms and  conditions, you are ready to sign up. Our usual lead time after signing  up is one month (there are cases of delays). Within this time, we  expect our customers to make arrangements for the circuits and  equipment. In cases where the AS number has not been obtained, it  should also be obtained within this period. At JPIX, we hold meetings  for the customer regarding the necessary arrangements until connection  with our engineer present (JPIX technical orientation).</p>
